Assistant to the President for Homeland Security and Counterterrorism, Lisa O. Monaco, met with the Chief of the Turkish National Intelligence Organization, Dr. Hakan Fidan, to discuss ways to enhance counterterrorism cooperation and involve Turkey in the international coalition against ISIL. Monaco expressed gratitude for Turkey's support in U.S. military operations in Iraq and Syria and emphasized the need for Turkey to increase their assistance to degrade and eliminate ISIL. They also discussed the importance of strengthening the capacity of Iraqi security forces and the moderate Syrian opposition, as well as improving border security to prevent the movement of foreign fighters. Both parties recognized the shared threat posed by al-Qa'ida veterans in Syria and agreed to continue consulting on security and intelligence matters.